Transcription.Text: 12. I The preacher have been king over Israel in Jerusalem. The author clearly intends to be taken as Solomon. The use of this literary device was really a means of expressing Qoheleth's conviction that neither wealth nor wisdom provided the clue to the final meaning of life.
